<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-12-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-12-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="723" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.50 Am 3/29: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Special Mission at Lausanne</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-12-12T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 12,
                                        1922—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>43. Mission’s 87, December 11, 2 p.m. Belief that you should carefully
                            avoid this question at Lausanne has our approval.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
